Source: das-toolbox
Section: utils
Priority: standard
Maintainer: rafael.levi@singularitynet.io
Build-Depends: build-essential, zlib1g-dev, python3-pip, python3 (>=3.8.0), debhelper (>=12.10ubuntu1), gzip
Standards-Version: 4.5.0

Package: das-toolbox
Architecture: any
Depends: docker.io | docker-ce, ${misc:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends}
Description: |
 This CLI provides a unified set of tools to manage the DAS ecosystem.
 This package bundles the das-cli, das-runner-manager, and gatekeeper tools.

 das-cli:
  Manage containerized services.
  Control OpenFaaS functions.
  Perform Metta operations (load and validate Metta files).

 das-runner-manager:
  Manage GitHub Actions self-hosted runners using Docker.
  Start, list, and stop runners for specific repositories.
  Includes tools to build runner manager binaries using Docker.

 gatekeeper:
  A lightweight and extensible system for managing reserved ports
  and registered instances across distributed infrastructure.
